1
00:00:03,408 --> 00:00:06,551
A saying of Descartes:
“Cogito, ergo sum.”

2
00:00:09,130 --> 00:00:11,015
Because I think,

3
00:00:11,015 --> 00:00:17,555
I can understand from that
that I exist;

4
00:00:17,785 --> 00:00:19,371
“I think, therefore I am.”

5
00:00:19,540 --> 00:00:22,928
[I Feel Therefore I Seek]

6
00:00:22,972 --> 00:00:27,216
But that’s sat and chit.

7
00:00:27,216 --> 00:00:31,959
Sat, meaning existence,
existential position.

8
00:00:31,959 --> 00:00:37,650
Chit: cognisance 
or awareness that I exist.

9
00:00:37,650 --> 00:00:41,640
This is what separates us
from inert matter.

10
00:00:41,640 --> 00:00:45,664
The chair, the table exist,

11
00:00:45,664 --> 00:00:50,279
but they have no awareness
of their existence.

12
00:00:50,279 --> 00:00:52,067
We can observe them,

13
00:00:52,067 --> 00:00:54,885
because we’re
conscious observers,

14
00:00:54,885 --> 00:01:00,133
and we can by this 
conscious observing principle

15
00:01:00,133 --> 00:01:07,628
understand minimally
our own existence.

16
00:01:07,628 --> 00:01:17,385
Sat, chit, then a third aspect
comes into awareness.

17
00:01:17,385 --> 00:01:22,799
I exist for some purpose.

18
00:01:22,802 --> 00:01:26,899
It’s not that we live
in a vacuum.

19
00:01:26,931 --> 00:01:30,600
So, ānanda.

20
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:38,630
Sat-сhit-ānanda: pleasure,
happiness, joy, ecstasy.

21
00:01:39,030 --> 00:01:44,496
Consciousness allows me
to feel those things;

22
00:01:44,496 --> 00:01:47,255
consciousness allows me
to feel

23
00:01:47,255 --> 00:01:52,604
happiness, pleasure, joy,
ecstasy, love, affection.

24
00:01:53,434 --> 00:01:55,734
But then we have to 
also acknowledge:

25
00:01:55,734 --> 00:02:04,332
it also allows me to feel
sad, unhappy, pain, suffering.

